issue_body:
Found by Andrei [here](https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/pull/141340#discussion_r2763318089).

Seems like we don't mark mapping-conflicted fields with the `UNSUPPORTED` type.

A small reproducer using the csv spec data is
```
FROM (FROM sample_data), (FROM sample_data_str) | KEEP client_ip | LIMIT 1

{
...
  "columns" : [
    {
      "name" : "client_ip",
      "type" : "keyword"
    }
  ],
  "values" : [
    [
      null
    ]
  ]
}

```

vs.

```
FROM sample_data, sample_data_str | KEEP client_ip | LIMIT 1

{
...
  "columns" : [
    {
      "name" : "client_ip",
      "type" : "unsupported",
      "original_types" : [
        "ip",
        "keyword"
      ],
      "suggested_cast" : "keyword"
    }
  ],
  "values" : [
    [
      null
    ]
  ]
}

```

### Description

The `tasks.json` reports a shard's `sessionId` and `sessionId` in its `description` from code

https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/db7821369207a1abb5a777cea8fef26af21172c3/server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/search/internal/ShardSearchContextId.java#L78

